About Us
Kelly's RV Park
Gravel & Paved RV Sites Fully Equipped for Comfortable Living
Owners'
Story
Richard and Mary first started camping on vacations with family more than 55 years ago and fulfilled a lifelong dream when they bought Kelly's RV/MH Park in 2005. Our continuous goal is to provide every guest comfortable stays in a clean, safe, peaceful, and uplifting setting.
We welcome everyone to join us in experiencing our tranquil North Central Florida RV park located in the scenic Suwannee Valley.
We look forward to seeing you soon!
AMENITIES & RATES
Our
Values
At Kelly's RV/MH Park, these values guide every aspect of our operations.
VIEW SITE MAP
Community
We believe in fostering a sense of belonging for every guest who enters our park. Our community is built on mutual respect, camaraderie, and shared experiences. Whether you're staying for a night or a season, you're part of the Kelly's RV/MH Park family.
Nature Appreciation
Our deep respect for the natural world is at the heart of what we do. We are dedicated to preserving and sharing the beauty of Suwannee Valley's landscape, providing a space where guests can reconnect with nature and find solace in its wonders.
Pet-Friendly Harmony
Pets are cherished companions, and we uphold an environment where both human and animal guests feel safe and welcome. We promote responsible pet ownership and ensure that our park is a haven where all members of the family can enjoy their stay.
Customer Wellbeing
Your comfort and satisfaction are paramount. We are committed to providing clean, safe, and well-maintained accommodations, as well as exceptional service that caters to your needs. Your positive experience is our ultimate measure of success.
Continuous Improvement
We are dedicated to evolving and adapting to the changing needs of our guests. Through feedback, innovation, and an unwavering commitment to excellence, we constantly strive to enhance your experience and provide you with the best possible stay.
Upholding Excellence
We invite you to join us in embracing these principles as we create a haven of nature, community, and comfort for all who visit.
CALL NOW
EVENTS
Make your reservations now at Kelly's RV/MH Park for all of these upcoming local events. We're just down the road from Stephen Foster State Park. Spaces are limited! Contact us for current or planned events.
Examples of Year Round Events:
Holiday Events
BBQ events
Bingo
Poker
CLR game nights
AMENITIES & RATES
Join Our Story at Kelly's RV/MH Park!
As you learn about our journey, we invite you to become a part of it. Join our community of outdoor enthusiasts, pet lovers, and fellow travelers who have found solace and adventure at Kelly's RV/MH Park. Whether you're seeking a short escape or a long-term haven, we welcome you to experience the warmth, nature's beauty, and the sense of belonging that defines our park.

Year-Round RV Park for those Who Enjoy the Outdoors
Kelly's RV/ MH Park
Bring your RV or motor home to Kelly's RV/MH Park for an overnight stay or become a resident of our friendly community with fun events. Open for more than two decades and easily accessible from both I-10 and I-75, our family-run RV park in White Springs, Florida features 20 acres of oversized sites that can accommodate up to a 55-foot trailer or motor home. Many of the RV sites are paved and all sites have 30/50 amp electric, water and sewer. We offer daily, weekly, or monthly
rates
(lowest in the area) and cabin rentals.
BOOK WITH US TODAY!
Contact us: (386) 397-2616
KellysRV@windstream.net
White Springs FL 32096
Welcome to
Kelly's RV Park!
At Kelly's RV/MH Park, we offer a year-round RV park nestled in the serene Suwannee Valley of White Springs, Florida. Our family-run park has been in operation for over two decades and is easily accessible from both I-10 and I-75. Whether you're looking for an overnight stay or seeking to become a long-term resident, we have something for everyone.
You can find gas and diesel fuel within a mile and ample shopping opportunities just 11 miles away in Lake City which also features a variety of restaurants. In addition, we are close to Disney World™ and the major cities of Jacksonville and Gainesville.
LEARN MORE
Various Local Activities
Come explore the amazing variety of native trees, plants, and wildlife that share this property. Teeming with pines and lush live oaks draped in beautiful Spanish moss, our park is surrounded by woods filled with tropical palmetto palms and extensive hiking trails. The Historic Suwannee River is located just one mile away, and the Suwannee Valley is noted for its wide range of outdoor activities, especially hunting and fishing. People frequently visit for hiking, biking, and canoeing as well. Regardless of the season, it's always a joy to become immersed in the natural beauty of our local area.
AMENITIES & RATES
Why Choose
Us:
Serene Natural Haven
The lush woods, extensive hiking trails, and the nearby Historic Suwannee River create a perfect backdrop for outdoor enthusiasts.
Spacious Accommodations
With paved RV sites, full hookups, and a range of amenities, you can relax knowing that your stay will be both convenient and pleasant.
Accessible and Convenient
Enjoy a short drive to the bustling city of Lake City for shopping and dining, or venture to major cities like Jacksonville and Gainesville for a change of scenery.
Experience Nature's Tranquility at Kelly's RV/MH Park!
Embark on your journey to outdoor bliss and create unforgettable memories amidst the beauty of Suwannee Valley. Whether you're seeking a short getaway or a new community to call home, Kelly's RV/MH Park is your haven. Book your spot today and discover the perfect blend of natural splendor, modern comfort, and a welcoming atmosphere.
BOOK WITH US TODAY
Get In Touch
(386) 397-2616
